			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1313')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=56749&amp;TOPIC_ID=6863&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=why+do+u+like+the+necro+class+so+much%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>It is who I am, it is what I play.  I have played the role of a Necromancer in so many RPGs that I can't keep count of it.  I may try my hand at other classes, but I always come back to the Necromancer.</P><P>"Time is meaningless to one who lives forever."<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>That's how I've been with playing Rangers, although EQ has actually changed my opinion.  I do love my ranger but this is the first time I've actually played an evil character.  I like being evil much better.  I have a second account cleric and then there's me, a now 49 Necro.  I am pretty sure that the next RPG I play that I am going to pick a Necromancer as the first character I devote any real time to.  </P><P>So getting back to the topic, the reason I like playing a necro so much is that at least for me they the "Total Package."  Utterly self-reliant, excellent soloers (imho the all around best in the game), very difficult to kill if played well, and the best part - evil, evil that is as evil as evil can get.  I can't be evil in real life, but I can take great pleasure in causing murder and mayhem in Norrath.</P><P>I always wonder when people complain about not being able to get groups.  I don't doubt that they are having trouble finding groups, I just wonder why they care.  I never group when I want XP and I find that I make plenty of friends along the way that I'm generally asked to group more often than I'd like. </P><P>Being evil, like Iksar evil can have it's perils.  The lower levels in particular can be difficult, however that pain turns to joy as you advance.  I used to run from SGT Slate in EC, or the gate gards and druids in WC, now they run from me.  I'm not trying to suggest you have to be Iksar or even a necro to be evil like I'm talking about, but factions are much more important to good classes/races than to evils.  I kill pretty much anything I want, but unless I start going after something that damages my Cabilis faction I have -zero- faction worries from the perspective of who my next victim is, quests not withstanding.  You can do this as any race you want in all honesty, as long as you keep faction with at least one of your trainers until you no longer need them (I'd call that level 60 just so you can spend your last points.)  </P><P>I love the image and concept of a Necro, drawing power from death.  There is a novel by Larry Niven called "The Magic Goes Away" that treats mana like a natural resource that get's spent.  As the ages pass and the mana starts to approach depletion, the old powerful magics start to fade and necromancy is the last viable method of harnessing mana for use, through the destruction of life.  When I started my necro that is the image I had and still do have: a caster whose power is stolen from and advanced through the death of others.</P><P><BR>Just as a side idea based on this view of necromancy:  Imagine if we got a spell that gave group members mana for everything the group got xp on, now that would rock and as long as it stacked with Lich it would help restore our lead in the mana regeneration department.  </P><P></P><P><b>I AM the angry leeezurd!</b></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22254" target="_blank" target="_blank">Sssyx Syxyx</a></P><P><a href="mailto:sssyx@mmdog.com">sssyx@mmdog.com</a></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
